==Swahili==
===Etymology===
From the [[w:Arabic language|Arabic]] word (''sahel'') in its plural form, (''sawahil'') (adj. ''coastal dwellers''). The ''[[ki-]]'' prefix is the language noun class of the Kiswahili language. The ''-i'' suffix is said by some to be Arabic's [[nisba]], but by others to be for [[phonetic]] reasons.
===Noun===
'''Kiswahili'''

# an [[agglutinative]] [[Bantu]] [[language]] widely spoken in East Africa

